    }
    db.deleteSession(args.session_id);
    db.deleteSessionMeta(args.session_id);
    result = { deleted: args.session_id };
    break;
  }
  ```

**What it does:**
1. Sanitizes tmux session name based on session_id
2. Kills the tmux session if it exists
3. Constructs path to JSONL conversation file
4. Deletes JSONL file from disk (fails silently for temp sessions with no file)
5. Removes session record from DB
6. Removes session metadata from cache
7. Returns confirmation of deletion

